content.description: ED: closed to climbing - this is a State Natural Area Follows a crack up the right side of the cliff. Bottom section is less than vertical, middle section is vertical, and top is slightly overhanging. Crux is near the anchor, where the crack is off-width and overhanging. This portion can be climbed around to the right. Anchor should sit in the fissure on the top of the cliff to be centered in the crack.
content.protection: build top rope anchor on trees
content.location: Obvious crack located about 25 ft to the right of the portion of the cliff that touches the lake.

content.description: This is an 80 ft. cliff overlooking Cox Hollow Lake. The entire area is covered in pine trees, so there are some pine needles on ledges and in cracks. The rock is highly featured, which allows for unique holds, but as it is mostly unclimbed, many could potentially break off.ED: State Natural Area: no climbing allowed
